pageContext.claim: “You know, the opposing -- the opposition party as the expression goes. They burned down the church the day before. I heard how nice and wonderful the protestors were over there. Really? Then why did they burn down the church the day before? They burned down a big section of it.”
pageContext.analysis: There's no evidence protestors tried to burn down St. John's Episcopal Church in Washington, which is near the White House. It was not a major fire. Only a small nursery in the basement was damaged; the main sanctuary was unharmed.
